<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=747" TARGET=_self>Think Again...</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>time will tell and i hope you're right (i'm doubting it tho)....you won't be able to satisying k3wLd00d without slackening the rules which will, in the end, harm the RP PvP segment....you're a GM, allu can do is tweak and fudge numbers, you ain't be gonna adding/removing features.................but it seems you also are very willing to see past any point i may be making to jump on the bandwagon of deriding the unpopular opinion so i figure, as much as i would LIKE to be able to enjoy a PvP game, i'll have to leave the PvP server to become the land of serial killers and go play on the regular servers...sigh....can i just sat one more time that me arguing position different than yours does not constitute a flame on my part...but it's a moot point, this is likely the last you'll hear from me (hold down the applause).......i tried to bring another viewpoint to light and i failed.......

<P>&gt; First off, lets start by saying: You're talking about my
<BR>&gt; project. So I'm not all enthused that you're killing it off
<BR>&gt; before we've even begun to make progress. Hell, I haven't even
<BR>&gt; gotten my Character set up on the PvP server yet. I see so many
<BR>&gt; people willing to pull the gun out on PvP because of this reason
<BR>&gt; and that reason. I've also heard some very nice ideas as far as
<BR>&gt; PvP goes, ones that I think would make a difference in the PvP
<BR>&gt; play. Lets not be too hasty. Oh and guys, to keep from looking a
<BR>&gt; bit silly. Try using titles like "Why I think PvP is
<BR>&gt; doomed" not "Why PvP is doomed". No one person
<BR>&gt; here is the expert on PvP, especially not in EQ. EQ is uncharted
<BR>&gt; territory.
<P>&gt; Geiger
